trace.verification_evidence:
{
  "red_failure_evidence": "Before the work the verify failed at the byte-identity check with 'No such file or directory' for BOTH skill roots, exit 1 - neither dispatch-prompt.md existed. That is precisely the shipped state of slice 1: control-loop.sh resolves ../references/<role>-prompt.md at line 113 and bootstrap-cockpit.sh starts the dispatch loop, so a cockpit started at that moment would have printed 'prompt file not found' every 60 seconds and, per D19's no-exit-on-error property, continued forever doing nothing.",
  "green_evidence": "PROMPT_WIRED / rc=0, re-run independently by the orchestrator. The verify is not a file-existence check: it puts a stub claude on PATH and runs one real control-loop iteration, so it proves the prompt is resolved and passed to the invocation, and asserts the 'prompt file not found' branch is not taken.",
  "orchestrator_review": "This is the third instance in this feature of the same failure shape - a piece named in one cell's prose as out of scope, with no later cell owning it. The first two were caught by the review panel; this one survived because every cell verify was scoped to its own file, so nothing checked that the assembled system could run. The prompt itself is deliberately 12 lines: it routes into the skill's dispatch role and sets the cold-start frame, and does not restate the procedure, which would have created a second copy free to drift."
}
